In fact it is the 125th most popular website in the World.

00:01:34.630 --> 00:01:39.490
People read The Daily Mail for all sorts of reasons, but it is

00:01:39.510 --> 00:01:44.420
particularly happy to publish articles “revealing” medical discoveries.

00:01:45.400 --> 00:01:51.630
“A glass of wine a day is NOT good for your health”, it revealed in October of 2018.

00:01:52.650 --> 00:01:58.740
Then ”Drinking a small glass of red wine a day could help avoid age-related health problems

00:01:58.880 --> 00:02:05.610
like diabetes, Alzheimer's and heart disease, study finds“, published in April of 2020

00:02:07.140 --> 00:02:14.430
“Drinking two glasses of wine per day may LOWER chance of developing dementia”, in February of 2023.

00:02:15.780 --> 00:02:21.870
If you were to add up everything that The Daily Mail said studies proved would cause cancer,

00:02:22.300 --> 00:02:28.960
you’d have at least 116 different items, and you could probably find just as many articles

00:02:29.240 --> 00:02:34.670
published in the same newspaper about the same items saying that they were good for your health.

00:02:36.190 --> 00:02:42.975
This has become a bit of a joke in British culture, but it does raise an interesting question about

00:02:42.985 --> 00:02:50.005
the basis of scientific studies, and how the results are published and presented to the public.

00:02:51.355 --> 00:02:56.945
Now, for the absence of doubt, this episode is not intended to suggest that any

00:02:56.945 --> 00:03:02.615
scientist is intentionally deceiving members of the public with a result of their study.

00:03:03.475 --> 00:03:08.665
Scientists and researchers do wonderful work, tirelessly furthering human

00:03:08.695 --> 00:03:13.939
understanding of everything from medicine to nutrition to the origins of the universe.

00:03:14.975 --> 00:03:21.245
What’s more, the peer review process is an effective safeguard for low quality research.

00:03:22.025 --> 00:03:27.245
To publish an article in a journal, you present your research methodology and results in detail.

00:03:27.905 --> 00:03:34.305
Then, other well-respected scientists have the chance to question and interrogate the process.

00:03:35.435 --> 00:03:40.195
This typically means that any scientific study that has large holes in

00:03:40.195 --> 00:03:45.285
it, that has not been conducted in a thorough and correct manner will not

00:03:45.335 --> 00:03:49.322
see the light of day, it will not be published in a reputable journal.

00:03:50.742 --> 00:03:52.962
Typically, but not always.

00:03:53.892 --> 00:03:59.082
So in this episode we are going to look at three occasions when this was not the case.

